SKILL|jupyter-live-kernel|"Iterative Python via live Jupyter kernel (hamelnb)."
STEP|1|Rule of thumb:** If you'd want a Jupyter notebook for the task, use this skill.
STEP|2|**uv** must be installed (check: `which uv`)
STEP|3|**JupyterLab** must be installed: `uv tool install jupyterlab`
STEP|4|A Jupyter server must be running (see Setup below)
STEP|5|**First execution after server start may timeout** — the kernel needs a moment
STEP|6|**The kernel Python is JupyterLab's Python** — packages must be installed in
STEP|7|**--compact flag saves significant tokens** — always use it. JSON output can
STEP|8|**For pure REPL use**, create a scratch.ipynb and don't bother with cell editing.
STEP|9|**Argument order matters** — subcommand flags like `--path` go BEFORE the
STEP|10|**If a session doesn't exist yet**, you need to start one via the REST API
STEP|11|**Errors are returned as JSON** with traceback — read the `ename` and `evalue`
STEP|12|**Occasional websocket timeouts** — some operations may timeout on first try,
